{
  "stem": "26276.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I couldn't tell you because we hardly would get in contact with anybody around the surrounded area of the bombarding.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And on top of it, we were guarded very, very close.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The German SS, with the dogs, so you couldn't-- you couldn't get close to anybody.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the biggest fun was when they bombarded some warehouses, where they had food prepared for the Germans to towards the front lines.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There we had the best time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There we had everything that we wanted.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Even bombarded, we had cookies, chocolates, cigarettes, candies, everything you want to think of.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know, the magazine-- you know, the warehouses.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That's supposed to be shipped out towards the front line for the front line soldiers.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Gross-Rosen.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Like I told you before, the atrocities that I saw in there with the children's clothes laid in the front of barracks.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was-- that hit it so hard, terrible, because we knew that those children were either gassed in Gross-Rosen or they were gassed and killed in other camps.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they brought in all the food-- all the clothes, with all the shoes, with all the glasses-- eyeglasses.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Everything to that camp, and we saw, in the front of the line of the barracks, lined up, such a big, big mountains of it.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That could make-- it made you sick looking at it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Six years.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] From '39 until I was liberated in May 1945.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- you know, when I became friends with the soldier that liberated me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Jerome Klein.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I stayed in Dachau until he was shipped out to Munich, which it was, I think, two weeks later.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He took me with him.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
